1
00:00:05,933 --> 00:00:07,767
<i>You're different from all
the women I've ever met.</i>

2
00:00:07,900 --> 00:00:10,133
<i> You men are all the same.</i>

3
00:00:10,267 --> 00:00:11,367
<i> Just because she's the help</i>

4
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:13,767
<i>doesn't mean you get
to treat her like that.</i>

5
00:00:13,900 --> 00:00:15,967
<i>Fine. Go ahead, be the hero,
Marj.</i>

6
00:00:16,100 --> 00:00:18,533
<i>I'll just keep going
after your husband.</i>

7
00:00:18,667 --> 00:00:19,667
<i> Hello?</i>

8
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:20,667
<i> Let's take a raincheck.</i>

9
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:21,400
<i> What?</i>

10
00:00:21,533 --> 00:00:22,667
<i> I'm with Marj.</i>

11
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:24,100
<i>You need all the help
you can get.</i>

12
00:00:24,233 --> 00:00:27,667
<i>Why don't you ask Evelyn
and Jobert to come back here?</i>

13
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:28,900
<i> Thanks dad.</i>

14
00:00:29,033 --> 00:00:30,633
<i> This really helps me a lot.</i>

15
00:00:30,767 --> 00:00:31,433
<i> Hello!</i>

16
00:00:31,567 --> 00:00:32,733
<i> It's easier to move</i>

17
00:00:32,867 --> 00:00:34,733
<i>when you don't have that much
stuff, right?</i>

18
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:37,133
<i>Oscar, take their things
to the guest room.</i>

19
00:00:37,267 --> 00:00:38,533
<i> The one near the laundry area.</i>

20
00:00:38,667 --> 00:00:41,700
<i>Maybe it's better
if we don't force ourselves</i>

21
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:43,100
<i> to stay here.</i>

22
00:00:43,233 --> 00:00:44,767
<i> We'll just leave, Marj.</i>

23
00:00:46,667 --> 00:00:48,067
Paolo, just let them go.

24
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:50,567
Let them do whatever they want.

25
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:52,233
Mom, please stop.

26
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:54,733
What's going on here?

27
00:00:58,367 --> 00:01:01,867
Evelyn, why are you leaving?

28
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:06,267
Regina...

29
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:08,200
What did you do?

30
00:01:08,367 --> 00:01:09,900
Did you tell them to leave?

31
00:01:10,867 --> 00:01:13,167
No, I was just welcoming them.

32
00:01:13,300 --> 00:01:16,000
Maybe they realized
they're not comfortable

33
00:01:16,133 --> 00:01:17,200
with the setup.

34
00:01:17,333 --> 00:01:20,800
I even told Evelyn they
could stay near the laundry area

35
00:01:20,933 --> 00:01:22,967
so she'd feel more at home.

36
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:24,933
She's the one who decided
to leave.

37
00:01:25,067 --> 00:01:26,900
I didn't tell her to go.

38
00:01:27,033 --> 00:01:29,167
Well, they're not leaving.

39
00:01:29,300 --> 00:01:30,600
And they're definitely
not staying

40
00:01:30,733 --> 00:01:32,433
next to the laundry area.

41
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:35,700
They're staying in the proper
guest rooms.

42
00:01:37,133 --> 00:01:39,633
But Greg, those are
for special guests.

43
00:01:40,967 --> 00:01:42,067
Exactly.

44
00:01:43,133 --> 00:01:45,700
They're Marj's family,
so they're special guests here.

45
00:01:47,667 --> 00:01:49,467
Marj and I already agreed
on this.

46
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:54,133
And as the head of the family,
I want everyone to feel welcome.

47
00:01:55,367 --> 00:01:57,933
From now on, I don't want
to hear any more insults

48
00:01:58,067 --> 00:02:00,900
or disrespect toward them.

49
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:03,433
Is that clear?

50
00:02:04,367 --> 00:02:05,933
Yes, Sir.

51
00:02:10,900 --> 00:02:12,033
Marj, go on.

52
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:14,900
Okay.

53
00:02:15,033 --> 00:02:16,267
- Let's go.
- Come on.

54
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:18,467
- Let's head to the guest room.
- Oscar, take their things back.

55
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:20,200
- Hello, Yolly.
- Let's go.

56
00:02:20,333 --> 00:02:21,233
Thank you.

57
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:38,500
We're not done yet, Evelyn.

58
00:03:31,267 --> 00:03:34,133
Sis, I'm scared.

59
00:03:34,267 --> 00:03:36,200
Mom, bro.

60
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:42,033
Mom, just bear with them.

61
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:46,267
You're right, Marj.

62
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,400
Let's just bear with them.

63
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,800
So they won't have anything bad
to say about us

64
00:03:51,933 --> 00:03:53,133
especially about you.

65
00:03:54,233 --> 00:03:55,267
Mom, thank you.

66
00:03:57,467 --> 00:04:00,633
Honestly, If I didn't
feel sorry for you,

67
00:04:00,767 --> 00:04:05,000
with everything
you're going through,

68
00:04:05,133 --> 00:04:09,633
we wouldn't insist on staying
in this house.

69
00:04:10,467 --> 00:04:13,233
Your mother in law really
makes us feel

70
00:04:13,367 --> 00:04:15,300
like we don't belong here.

71
00:04:18,367 --> 00:04:20,767
Mom, thank you so much
for being here.

72
00:04:21,467 --> 00:04:25,467
Now that you're beside me,
I know I can handle everything.

73
00:04:39,233 --> 00:04:42,167
Thank you for coming with me
earlier

74
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:45,433
and standing up for Mom
and Jobert.

75
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:51,867
Can we get some rest now?

76
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,400
I've got an early
meeting tomorrow.

77
00:04:56,233 --> 00:04:58,267
All right, let's go to the room.

78
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,667
But give me a kiss first.

79
00:05:10,633 --> 00:05:11,500
Sorry!

80
00:05:12,367 --> 00:05:13,567
I was texting.

81
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:15,533
Oh my gosh, I almost fell...

82
00:05:15,667 --> 00:05:16,967
By the way, Paolo...

83
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:19,700
your client was waiting
for you at the hotel earlier.

84
00:05:21,867 --> 00:05:24,267
You had a client meeting today?

85
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:25,967
Yes.

86
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:29,833
He canceled last minute.

87
00:05:29,967 --> 00:05:31,533
The client was pretty upset,

88
00:05:31,667 --> 00:05:34,900
he was expecting that Paolo
will be there.

89
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:39,167
All the client's effort
went to waste.

90
00:05:40,967 --> 00:05:44,067
But you said you were
going to the gym.

91
00:05:46,033 --> 00:05:47,900
Yeah...

92
00:05:48,033 --> 00:05:51,233
I forgot I had a client meeting.

93
00:05:51,367 --> 00:05:55,367
I already apologized via text.

94
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:57,800
I only remembered when
we were on the way.

95
00:05:57,933 --> 00:06:02,133
But I chose to go with you
to pick up your family.

96
00:06:02,267 --> 00:06:04,500
Because I know that's more
important to you.

97
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:17,300
Paolo, you better better
make it up to that client.

98
00:06:17,433 --> 00:06:20,167
If they get mad, that's on you.

99
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:49,567
Evelyn...

100
00:06:53,867 --> 00:06:55,733
What are you doing here?

101
00:06:58,767 --> 00:07:00,500
Someone might see you!

102
00:07:01,167 --> 00:07:02,767
Can you just leave?

103
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:07,867
I'm not leaving until we talk.

104
00:07:09,333 --> 00:07:11,367
You've been avoiding me
for weeks.

105
00:07:16,067 --> 00:07:18,867
What do you really want?

106
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:22,400
Why are you insisting
we stay here?

107
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:25,933
What are you doing?

108
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,533
I just want to be with you.

109
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,667
You keep avoiding me.

110
00:07:37,667 --> 00:07:40,067
I've tried talking to you
so many times.

111
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:42,067
But there's no chance at all.

112
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:46,633
This was the only way
I could see you everyday,

113
00:07:46,767 --> 00:07:49,433
where you can't avoid me.

114
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:52,133
Is that how you see me?

115
00:07:53,667 --> 00:07:59,700
You think I'd agree to be
your mistress

116
00:07:59,833 --> 00:08:03,767
under the same roof
as your wife?

117
00:08:10,133 --> 00:08:12,167
Weren't you supposed to stay
overnight

118
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:13,900
with Lalaine and your friends?

119
00:08:18,467 --> 00:08:20,733
No, I didn't go.

120
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:24,733
I worked overtime to fix
the company's problems.

121
00:08:24,867 --> 00:08:26,533
You know things are a mess
right now, right?

122
00:08:26,667 --> 00:08:28,167
Really?

123
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:30,833
Or are you fixing
the mess Paolo made?

124
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:35,700
You know, Thea...

125
00:08:35,833 --> 00:08:37,167
sometimes I don't understand
you.

126
00:08:38,067 --> 00:08:41,967
You spend more time helping
Paolo fix his problems

127
00:08:42,100 --> 00:08:43,033
than being with this family.

128
00:08:44,933 --> 00:08:46,300
You're forgetting
your responsibilities here.

129
00:08:47,533 --> 00:08:49,800
With me as your husband.

130
00:08:52,267 --> 00:08:56,033
Sometimes it feels like you'd
rather be with Paolo than me.

131
00:08:57,067 --> 00:08:59,567
Oh please, Edward.

132
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:03,400
Don't tell me you're jealous
of your own brother.

133
00:09:04,300 --> 00:09:06,200
What is all this to you, Greg?

134
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,200
A game?

135
00:09:09,100 --> 00:09:10,567
This isn't a game.

136
00:09:11,567 --> 00:09:12,933
I like you, Evelyn.

137
00:09:14,333 --> 00:09:18,233
And stop pretending
you don't feel anything for me.

138
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:22,400
Please, just stop!

139
00:09:23,633 --> 00:09:26,100
Don't drag me into your mess.

140
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:31,400
I'm here because of Jasmine.

141
00:09:32,133 --> 00:09:34,833
Because my grandchild
and my child needs me.

142
00:09:36,733 --> 00:09:43,133
If you still have any
respect for me, please...

143
00:09:43,267 --> 00:09:44,600
stay away from me.

144
00:09:45,467 --> 00:09:47,267
Please!

145
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:10,433
I'm only doing this to make us
look good in Dad's eyes.

146
00:10:11,133 --> 00:10:13,567
I have no choice but help Paolo.

147
00:10:13,700 --> 00:10:17,633
If the company recovers,
we all benefit, right?

148
00:10:17,767 --> 00:10:22,100
Why are you sure Paolo's
going to succeed?

149
00:10:23,267 --> 00:10:25,033
Of course.

150
00:10:25,167 --> 00:10:26,900
I believe in him.

151
00:10:29,967 --> 00:10:31,200
Wow, you really admire him.

152
00:10:32,367 --> 00:10:35,333
I wish I could feel
that from you sometimes.

153
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:36,867
That you actually
believe in me.

154
00:10:38,033 --> 00:10:39,467
Because in case you forgot...

155
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:40,867
I'm your husband.

156
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:41,900
Not him.

157
00:10:49,867 --> 00:10:51,333
Drama!

158
00:11:32,567 --> 00:11:34,433
You guys are actually
fun to watch.

159
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:36,800
Looks like you're really
enjoying yourselves,

160
00:11:36,933 --> 00:11:39,067
and it's just a simple
breakfast.

161
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:42,167
Feels like a whole feast
for you.

162
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:49,100
We're just appreciating
the blessings, Ma.

163
00:11:49,833 --> 00:11:50,833
Well, you've got a point.

164
00:11:50,967 --> 00:11:54,767
I mean, if you suddenly
moved into a nicer place,

165
00:11:54,900 --> 00:11:58,133
you'd probably be thanking
the Lord too, right?

166
00:11:58,267 --> 00:12:01,900
But I'm really happy you
adjusted quickly here.

167
00:12:03,267 --> 00:12:04,600
Regina, please...

168
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:07,200
Just let them eat in peace.

169
00:12:15,233 --> 00:12:19,000
Anyway dad, I'm holding
an open house party tomorrow

170
00:12:19,133 --> 00:12:20,467
at Menagerie.

171
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:24,733
It's to attract more potential
buyers for the units.

172
00:12:26,133 --> 00:12:28,533
Love, can I come with you?

173
00:12:29,533 --> 00:12:32,400
I can call some of
my former clients.

174
00:12:32,533 --> 00:12:35,800
I'm sure they'd be interested.
They might want to get a unit.

175
00:12:38,067 --> 00:12:39,367
Love there's no need.

176
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:41,100
Thea and I can handle it.

177
00:12:41,933 --> 00:12:44,000
Paolo, please, let me do this.

178
00:12:44,967 --> 00:12:46,667
So we can reconnect again.

179
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:50,400
I just feel like you're slowly
drifting away from me.

180
00:12:52,233 --> 00:12:55,400
Marj, just stay here.

181
00:12:55,533 --> 00:12:57,633
Don't leave Jasmine.

182
00:12:57,767 --> 00:13:00,167
She needs you here
more than that party.

183
00:13:01,533 --> 00:13:05,867
Going to that event wouldn't
make me a bad mom.

184
00:13:08,233 --> 00:13:09,933
Don't be so defensive.

185
00:13:10,067 --> 00:13:11,800
I'm just concerned
about Jasmine.

186
00:13:11,933 --> 00:13:14,167
Then why don't you focus
your concern

187
00:13:14,300 --> 00:13:16,233
on your own child and husband?

188
00:13:17,433 --> 00:13:20,000
Aren't you the one who's always
away from home?

189
00:13:22,033 --> 00:13:23,467
Thea, that's enough!

190
00:13:24,467 --> 00:13:25,733
You have to stop!

191
00:13:25,867 --> 00:13:27,600
Even you, Edward?

192
00:13:27,733 --> 00:13:29,800
Why are you siding with Marj
instead of me?

193
00:13:30,367 --> 00:13:31,400
Stop it!

194
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,400
We have guests here.

195
00:13:42,433 --> 00:13:46,133
At least let me keep a little
dignity in front of Evelyn.

196
00:13:53,033 --> 00:13:54,067
Please!

197
00:14:16,533 --> 00:14:18,900
How many times do
I have to tell you?

198
00:14:19,033 --> 00:14:20,333
Stop attacking Marj!

199
00:14:21,367 --> 00:14:22,567
You're just looking
for trouble.

200
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:26,767
You're trying to create cracks,
so we get exposed!

201
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:29,833
But Paolo, I can't help it.

202
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:30,967
I'm upset.

203
00:14:32,667 --> 00:14:34,733
It's been so long
since we made love.

204
00:14:35,433 --> 00:14:37,000
You always leave me hanging.

205
00:14:38,833 --> 00:14:39,800
Can you stop, Thea?

206
00:14:40,533 --> 00:14:42,533
When we started this,

207
00:14:42,667 --> 00:14:46,500
I told you, no demands,
no drama.

208
00:14:46,633 --> 00:14:48,133
So can you get it together?

209
00:14:52,833 --> 00:14:53,967
Fine.

210
00:15:03,267 --> 00:15:06,000
I'm not demanding anything.

211
00:15:07,367 --> 00:15:09,500
It's just a request, Paolo.

212
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:14,867
Don't bring Marj along,
so we can be together.

213
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:18,067
That's not possible.

214
00:15:18,900 --> 00:15:22,333
You saw how determined she
is in front of Dad, right?

215
00:15:22,467 --> 00:15:26,700
If I stop her,
she'll get suspicious.

216
00:15:30,900 --> 00:15:33,133
We'll lose our chance even more.

217
00:15:41,567 --> 00:15:43,033
Mom, look.

218
00:15:43,167 --> 00:15:44,700
- Does this look okay?
- Wow!

219
00:15:44,833 --> 00:15:47,233
- It's beautiful!
- It looks good, Marj!

220
00:15:47,367 --> 00:15:48,633
It suits you well.

221
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:52,900
I just want Paolo
to notice me, Mom.

222
00:15:53,767 --> 00:15:56,633
I want what we had before.

223
00:15:56,767 --> 00:15:58,900
When we were happy...

224
00:15:59,033 --> 00:16:02,033
getting along,
helping each other,

225
00:16:02,167 --> 00:16:04,100
giving to each other.

226
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:07,900
It feels like he's still distant
from me.

227
00:16:08,067 --> 00:16:10,067
Our relationship still
isn't normal.

228
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:13,367
It's actually a good thing
he allowed me

229
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:14,933
to come with him today.

230
00:16:16,633 --> 00:16:18,067
You know, Marj...

231
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:22,733
maybe he really does want
to fix your relationship.

232
00:16:22,867 --> 00:16:25,500
Maybe you should go too.

233
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:32,400
Your sister in law might try
to ruin your image there.

234
00:16:34,733 --> 00:16:35,800
You know, Marj...

235
00:16:35,933 --> 00:16:39,300
something is off with her.

236
00:16:40,367 --> 00:16:41,933
Don't worry, Mom.

237
00:16:42,100 --> 00:16:44,367
I'll do everything I can
to fix things with Paolo.

238
00:16:45,667 --> 00:16:48,933
Jasmine really misses
how we used to be.

239
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:52,667
She's hoping her dad
will be okay again.

240
00:16:54,467 --> 00:16:55,867
Sis...

241
00:16:58,333 --> 00:17:01,733
Don't worry about Jasmine.

242
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:04,333
Have fun at the party.

243
00:17:04,467 --> 00:17:07,067
I will take care of her.

244
00:17:21,267 --> 00:17:22,267
Paolo!

245
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:25,500
What are you doing here?

246
00:17:25,633 --> 00:17:27,667
Marj might see you,
she'll get suspicious.

247
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:29,167
Relax.

248
00:17:29,300 --> 00:17:32,333
Your wife took Jasmine
for a check up.

249
00:17:32,467 --> 00:17:33,300
They won't be back for a while.

250
00:17:33,433 --> 00:17:34,400
So...

251
00:17:34,533 --> 00:17:37,967
we've got time for a little
afternoon delight.

252
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:39,267
You're so naughty.

253
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:41,167
Admit it...

254
00:17:41,300 --> 00:17:42,767
You like the thrill.

255
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:44,067
Yeah.

256
00:18:04,267 --> 00:18:05,967
Hush, keep it down.

257
00:18:06,100 --> 00:18:07,367
Come on, this place is huge.

258
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:09,300
No one's going to hear us.

259
00:18:32,100 --> 00:18:33,133
Oh my God!

260
00:18:33,267 --> 00:18:34,500
Oh my goodness!

261
00:18:36,733 --> 00:18:37,800
Seriously?

262
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:53,500
Oh my goodness!

263
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:55,633
Sir Paolo, I'm sorry,
I didn't know you were here.

264
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:57,433
I thought the room was empty.

265
00:18:57,567 --> 00:18:59,500
- Sorry.
- Next time, knock!

266
00:18:59,633 --> 00:19:01,600
Don't just walk in like that!

267
00:19:01,733 --> 00:19:03,800
I'm sorry, Sir.
It won't happen again.

268
00:19:05,567 --> 00:19:06,833
What are you waiting for?

269
00:19:06,967 --> 00:19:07,900
Get out!

270
00:19:08,033 --> 00:19:09,867
I was just going to
take the trash, sir.

271
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:11,133
No, don't!

272
00:19:11,267 --> 00:19:12,167
Don't touch that!

273
00:19:14,467 --> 00:19:17,167
Why? I'm just taking
the trash...

274
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:18,733
No, no, it's barely full.

275
00:19:18,867 --> 00:19:20,100
Just take it out later, okay?

276
00:19:20,233 --> 00:19:20,833
Go on, get out.

277
00:19:20,967 --> 00:19:22,767
I've got a lot to do.

278
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:23,567
Go on.

279
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:24,533
Yes, Sir.

280
00:19:24,667 --> 00:19:26,167
Sorry again, Sir.

281
00:19:30,700 --> 00:19:32,167
All right.

282
00:19:32,300 --> 00:19:33,700
I'm sorry, Sir.

283
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:51,267
Good thing we didn't get caught.

284
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:52,867
So can you leave now?

285
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,033
No way.

286
00:19:54,167 --> 00:19:55,867
You've left me hanging way
too many times already.

287
00:19:58,567 --> 00:19:59,633
Let's just be quick, okay?

288
00:20:27,633 --> 00:20:30,300
Nurse, I don't want that.

289
00:20:30,433 --> 00:20:33,033
It's bitter, I'm going
to throw up if I take that.

290
00:20:33,167 --> 00:20:35,200
But Jas, you need to take it.

291
00:20:35,367 --> 00:20:37,467
To make you feel better.

292
00:20:38,867 --> 00:20:41,067
It just makes me feel worse.

293
00:20:43,733 --> 00:20:45,133
Excuse me.

294
00:20:48,367 --> 00:20:52,200
Baby Jasmine, you need
to take your medicine.

295
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:54,733
Uncle, I can't...

296
00:20:54,867 --> 00:20:56,367
It's really bitter.

297
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:59,833
I know how to swallow medicine
easily.

298
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:03,200
My sister taught me how to take
medicine like this.

299
00:21:03,733 --> 00:21:05,600
This is what you have to do.

300
00:21:05,733 --> 00:21:08,533
You have to pinch your nose,
like this.

301
00:21:08,700 --> 00:21:11,500
Then swallow it.

302
00:21:13,667 --> 00:21:16,267
That's it. Just hang in there,
Baby Jasmine.

303
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:17,967
You can do it.

304
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:20,033
You have to bear it.

305
00:21:20,167 --> 00:21:22,967
Nurse, she's ready
to take her medicine.

306
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:30,033
Pinch your nose.

307
00:21:36,367 --> 00:21:38,300
Good job, Baby Jasmine!

308
00:21:39,567 --> 00:21:41,933
You did it!

309
00:21:42,100 --> 00:21:44,067
See? She did it!

310
00:21:45,767 --> 00:21:48,333
You're such a good teacher,
Uncle.

311
00:21:48,467 --> 00:21:50,800
I did it because of you.

312
00:21:50,933 --> 00:21:53,767
Baby Jasmine,
once you get better,

313
00:21:53,900 --> 00:21:56,067
Uncle Jobert will treat you,
okay?

314
00:21:56,200 --> 00:21:59,033
I'm a big boy now,
I've got a job.

315
00:21:59,167 --> 00:22:01,467
I can treat you!

316
00:22:02,500 --> 00:22:04,967
I'll get better
as fast as I can.

317
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:06,933
So we can hang out.

318
00:22:07,067 --> 00:22:10,800
We'll eat ice cream,
fried chicken...

319
00:22:10,933 --> 00:22:11,833
Ice cream!

320
00:22:11,967 --> 00:22:14,367
- I like that!
- Let's go out, okay, Uncle?

321
00:22:16,933 --> 00:22:18,633
Chocolate ice cream...

322
00:22:18,767 --> 00:22:19,633
so good!

323
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:23,833
- Take me with you too!
- Ashley can come!

324
00:22:26,300 --> 00:22:27,100
Good job!

325
00:22:27,967 --> 00:22:29,167
Thanks, uncle.

326
00:22:29,733 --> 00:22:34,833
Go ahead and eat, Pong,
it's good!

327
00:22:37,633 --> 00:22:39,267
- You don't want it?
- Hi!

328
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:43,000
You're Jasmine's Uncle, right?

329
00:22:43,133 --> 00:22:44,067
Yeah.

330
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:48,500
I'm Jobert, Jasmine's uncle.

331
00:22:48,667 --> 00:22:50,667
I'm Ashley.

332
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:53,233
Jasmine's cousin,
and her best friend.

333
00:22:53,367 --> 00:22:56,433
It's so nice to finally
meet you.

334
00:22:56,567 --> 00:22:58,600
She always talks about you.

335
00:23:00,667 --> 00:23:06,500
If you're Jasmine's friend,
then we're friends too.

336
00:23:06,633 --> 00:23:12,100
Yes. Even if we just met,
we both care about her.

337
00:23:13,133 --> 00:23:14,767
You're Pong's friend too...

338
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:15,433
Wait!

339
00:23:15,567 --> 00:23:16,600
I don't want to!

340
00:23:16,733 --> 00:23:18,367
- He's nice!
- Mommy, no, wait!

341
00:23:18,500 --> 00:23:19,467
Mommy, wait!

342
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:20,533
-You're scaring her, aren't you?
-Mommy, no.

343
00:23:20,667 --> 00:23:21,933
He's not hurting me!

344
00:23:22,100 --> 00:23:23,967
I just got surprised
by the turtle.

345
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:24,967
Stay away from her!

346
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:25,733
Mom, please, stop!

347
00:23:25,867 --> 00:23:28,167
You two shouldn't be together!

348
00:23:28,300 --> 00:23:31,067
You might catch his craziness!

349
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,267
What is going here?

350
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:33,133
Sis...

351
00:23:33,267 --> 00:23:34,933
Why are you picking
on my brother?

352
00:23:42,367 --> 00:23:45,800
Who gave you the right to yell
at my brother?

353
00:23:46,467 --> 00:23:47,600
Hold on, Marj.

354
00:23:47,733 --> 00:23:49,367
Calm down.

355
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:51,633
I didn't do anything wrong.

356
00:23:51,767 --> 00:23:55,867
I was just asking why Ashley
and Jobert were together.

357
00:23:56,033 --> 00:23:56,833
No.

358
00:23:56,967 --> 00:23:59,200
She was yelling at me earlier!

359
00:23:59,333 --> 00:24:01,300
You told me to stay away!

360
00:24:01,433 --> 00:24:02,933
You were yelling at me!

361
00:24:03,067 --> 00:24:05,200
Jobert, just calm down, okay?

362
00:24:05,333 --> 00:24:07,367
Jobert, I'm not mad.

363
00:24:07,500 --> 00:24:09,433
I just naturally
have a loud voice.

364
00:24:09,567 --> 00:24:11,600
It's not my fault
you misunderstood

365
00:24:11,733 --> 00:24:13,600
and you're being overly
sensitive.

366
00:24:13,733 --> 00:24:15,367
You can even ask Ashley.

367
00:24:16,867 --> 00:24:18,500
Thea, I know you.

368
00:24:18,633 --> 00:24:21,700
And I know my brother,
he doesn't lie.

369
00:24:21,833 --> 00:24:24,267
If you've got a problem with me,
then face me.

370
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:26,333
Take it out on me.

371
00:24:26,467 --> 00:24:27,533
Goodness!

372
00:24:27,667 --> 00:24:29,367
But the moment I see you
mistreating my brother again,

373
00:24:29,533 --> 00:24:30,733
you'll be dealing with me.

374
00:24:32,067 --> 00:24:33,100
Jobert, let's go.

375
00:24:42,233 --> 00:24:43,867
And you...

376
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:47,067
I don't want to see you
talking to that idiot,

377
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:48,900
do you understand?

378
00:24:49,033 --> 00:24:50,733
Stay away from that family.

379
00:24:54,633 --> 00:24:55,800
Yes, Mom.

380
00:25:11,167 --> 00:25:12,433
Yes, Ma'am.

381
00:25:12,567 --> 00:25:14,933
Ma'am Marj really went off
on Ma'am Thea.

382
00:25:16,100 --> 00:25:17,567
So that's how she is...

383
00:25:17,700 --> 00:25:20,867
when it comes to her brother,
she turns into a tiger.

384
00:25:21,700 --> 00:25:22,933
I knew it.

385
00:25:23,067 --> 00:25:24,567
They haven't even been
here that long,

386
00:25:24,700 --> 00:25:27,733
and Marj's family is already
creating trouble.

387
00:25:27,867 --> 00:25:31,600
I won't allow them to destroy
the peace in my household.

388
00:25:36,567 --> 00:25:41,267
I want you to keep an eye
on Evelyn and Jobert.

389
00:25:41,400 --> 00:25:44,700
And if you see them doing
anything wrong,

390
00:25:44,833 --> 00:25:46,133
report it to me immediately.

391
00:25:46,267 --> 00:25:47,400
Do we understand each other?

392
00:25:47,533 --> 00:25:49,833
Ma'am, are you asking me
to spy on them?

393
00:25:49,967 --> 00:25:51,033
Do you have a problem with that?

394
00:25:51,167 --> 00:25:51,667
No, Ma'am.

395
00:25:51,800 --> 00:25:52,600
All right, yes, Ma'am.

396
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:57,467
We need to find something
against them a mistake.

397
00:25:57,600 --> 00:25:59,900
So Greg will be forced
to kick them out.

398
00:26:09,500 --> 00:26:10,800
Hi, Marj.

399
00:26:10,933 --> 00:26:14,000
To be fair, you look
presentable tonight.

400
00:26:14,133 --> 00:26:15,267
But the question is...

401
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:17,200
can you keep top socially?

402
00:26:17,333 --> 00:26:21,200
Or you have gotten rusty staying
at home or the hospital.

403
00:26:21,333 --> 00:26:24,067
You know, no matter how long
I've been out of the scene,

404
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:27,300
I'll never forget my manners.

405
00:26:27,433 --> 00:26:31,500
It's tough when all you
have is beauty but no class.

406
00:26:31,633 --> 00:26:34,667
I guess that's what happens
when you're full of envy.

407
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:37,900
No matter how expensive
your outfit is,

408
00:26:38,033 --> 00:26:41,800
your attitude
still makes you look...

409
00:26:41,967 --> 00:26:46,000
cheap.

410
00:26:46,133 --> 00:26:48,567
I don't see anything wrong
with what I'm doing, Evelyn.

411
00:26:48,700 --> 00:26:51,533
You've spent your whole
life enduring a husband

412
00:26:51,667 --> 00:26:54,433
who gave you nothing
but pain and heartbreak.

413
00:26:54,567 --> 00:26:57,133
I just want you to feel
that you deserve more.

414
00:26:57,267 --> 00:26:58,067
Oh, no...

415
00:26:58,200 --> 00:27:00,633
Ma'am Evelyn is doing
something wrong.
